# Course Studio page layout (default template)

When creating or editing `*.page.v1.json` under `extension/src/webview/course-studio/content/`:

## Canonical reference

**`st-intro-core-ideas.page.v1.json`** — approved live-article layout (2026-06-11).

Starters: `template-live-article.page.v1.json`, `template-prose-only.page.v1.json`.  
Builders: `courseStudioPageTemplates.ts`.

## Live article stack (top → bottom)

1. **Heading** — full width (`columnSpan: 12`, rows 1–2)
2. **Callout** — full width (rows 3–4)
3. **Live widgets** — own row(s) from row 5 (horizontal strip or cards)
4. **Markdown** — full width below (`columnSpan: 12`, `readHeight: "content"`)

**Never** place dashboard widgets, telemetry cards, or widget-boards in columns 9–12 while markdown uses columns 1–8.

## Prose-only topics

Engineering / reference: markdown only, `columnSpan: 12`, `readHeight: "content"`. Optional heading above.

## Telemetry meta (live topics)

```json
"meta": {
  "telemetryPreference": "auto",
  "staleMs": 2000,
  "defaultLinkHealth": "freeze-gray"
}
```

## Docs

`extension/src/webview/course-studio/docs/COURSE_OUTLINE.md` § Default page template.

## Communication

**Always DO NOT respond in Chinese.** Use **English** and/or **Thai** only — `communication-language.mdc`.
